### Workout Tracker API - Example HTTP Requests
### Use with REST Client extensions in VS Code, IntelliJ IDEA, or similar tools

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000

### Get welcome message
GET {{baseUrl}}/

### Get all exercises
GET {{baseUrl}}/exercises

### Get specific exercise by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/exercises/1

### Get non-existent exercise (should return 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/exercises/9999

### Create a new exercise
POST {{baseUrl}}/exercises
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Deadlift",
  "sets": 5,
  "reps": 5,
  "weight": 135.0
}

### Create exercise without weight (optional field)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exercises
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Push Ups",
  "sets": 3,
  "reps": 15
}

### Create exercise with invalid data (should return 422)
POST {{baseUrl}}/exercises
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Invalid Exercise",
  "sets": "not_a_number",
  "reps": 10
}

### Update an exercise (partial update)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/exercises/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sets": 4,
  "reps": 12,
  "weight": 105.0
}

### Update only weight
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/exercises/2
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "weight": 25.0
}

### Update non-existent exercise (should return 404)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/exercises/9999
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "sets": 5
}

### Delete an exercise
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/exercises/3

### Delete non-existent exercise (should return 404)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/exercises/9999

### Workflow: Create, Read, Update, Delete
### 1. Create new exercise
POST {{baseUrl}}/exercises
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Lunges",
  "sets": 3,
  "reps": 10,
  "weight": 20.0
}

### 2. Get the newly created exercise (use ID from previous response)
GET {{baseUrl}}/exercises/7

### 3. Update the exercise
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/exercises/7
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "weight": 25.0
}

### 4. Delete the exercise
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/exercises/7

